<h2>2.2. Threats from software that the user do not control</h2>

<ul>
<li>There are only two options: the users controls the program OR the program controls the users</li>
<li>Backdoors and Universal Backdoors</li>
<li>Real-life examples: <a href="https://www.gnu.org/philosophy/why-call-it-the-swindle.html">Amazon Swindle</a>, portable phones</li>
</ul>


